# Commit Message Syntax

All commits MUST follow [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/) format used in this project.

## Format

```
type: PREFIX-### lowercase imperative description
```

Every commit message **must** include a ticket number immediately after the colon. Valid prefixes: `US-`, `USC-`, `DEV-`, `LF-` (each followed by digits).

## Allowed Types

| Type | When to use |
|------|-------------|
| `feat` | New feature or capability |
| `fix` | Bug fix |
| `refactor` | Code restructuring with no behavior change |
| `chore` | Maintenance, deps, scripts, config |
| `style` | Visual/UI-only changes (not code formatting) |
| `docs` | Documentation only |
| `test` | Adding or updating tests |
| `perf` | Performance improvement |

## Rules

- **Ticket number required**: every subject must start with a valid prefix (`US-`, `USC-`, `DEV-`, or `LF-`) followed by digits — `feat: US-42 add billing page`
- **No scope**: write `feat: US-42 add billing page`, NOT `feat(billing): US-42 add page`
- **Lowercase** after the ticket number — no capitalized first word
- **Imperative mood** — write "add", "fix", "remove", not "added", "fixes", "removed"
- **Single line** — no multi-line body or footer unless the user explicitly asks for one
- **Concise** — describe what changed in a short phrase, not a full sentence

## Examples

```
feat: US-42 add organization deactivation/reactivation for superadmins
fix: USC-118 resolve all non-Adyen TypeScript errors across the project
refactor: DEV-95 migrate ledger tables to reusable DataTable components
chore: LF-7 remove defunct User Signup quick link from superadmin sidebar
style: US-203 move Directory to top of Athletes section in admin sidebar
```
